  Category: Data transfer
    Move data between registers and memory.  MIPS is
    load/store — math never operates on memory directly.
    (COD §2.3, §2.9.)
  What it did:
    Load Upper Immediate — placed the 16-bit immediate into the
    upper 16 bits of $at, zeroing the lower 16. Often paired with
    `ori` to construct a full 32-bit constant.
