  Category: Logical
    Bitwise operations and shifts. (COD §2.6.)
  Modifiers in `ori`:
    `i` — immediate form: one operand is a 16-bit constant baked
          into the instruction word, not a register. Lets
          small constants be supplied without a separate
          load.
  What it did:
    OR Immediate — computed $at OR zero-extended immediate; the result was placed in $a0.
